-- 
BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Tombini and Mantega Speak at Seminar in Rio

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-26T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/brazil-daybook-tombini-and-mantega-speak-at-seminar-in-rio.html
Brazil central bank President
Alexandre Tombini and Finance Minister Guido Mantega speak at
the Managing Capital Flows in Emerging Markets conference in  Rio
de Janeiro , starting at 12:30 p.m. local time. Speakers also
include representatives of the  International Monetary Fund ,
local and international banks.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  has a signing ceremony at 11 a.m.,
meets with Minister for Agricultural Development Afonso Florense
at 3 p.m., and meets with Planning Minister Miriam Belchior at
4.30 p.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega speaks at the Managing Capital
Flows conference in Rio de Janeiro at 12:30 p.m. and has
internal meetings in the afternoon.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini participates in the
Managing Capital Flows conference in Rio de Janeiro.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Fiesp, the manufacturing association of the state of Sao Paulo,
and labor unions hold a conference about industrial production
and the job market. Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  is one of the
speakers in the afternoon. Trade Minister Fernando Pimentel,
Science & Technology Minister Aloizio Mercadante and Vice
President Michel Temmer are also attending. *Second day of the
17th Latin Oil Week conference in Rio de Janeiro, with
executives of oil and gas companies.
*BM&FBovespa holds seminar on agribusiness with Agriculture
Minister Wagner Rossi, CME Group VP Charles Carey, Agroconsult’s
director Andre Pessoa, ADM’s director Carsten Wegener, Marfrig’s
director Moacir Martins, Louis Dreyfus’s director Octavio Pires,
Unica’s president Marcos Jank, Glencore’s director Thomas von
Rymon and BM&FBovespa CEO Edemir Pinto. In Sao Paulo, starting
at 8 a.m.
*Vale’s IR director Roberto Castelo Branco to attend seminar in
Rio de Janeiro at 9 a.m.
*Press conference by ThyssenKrupp CSA VP Rodrigo Tostes and
Sustainability Director Luiz Claudio Castro, at 10:30 a.m.
*Unica industry association to release crushing report for the
first half of May, at 2 p.m.  ECONOMY:
*FGV construction costs at 8 a.m.
*Unemployment rate at 9 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Amil (AMIL3 BZ) agreed to buy Lincx for 170 million reais.
*JBS (JBSS3 B) said to be in talks for $800 million loan at 4.5%
a year.
*Tereos Internacional (TERI3 BZ) plans to raise up to 600
million reais in a primary share sale.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 0.1 percent to 63,388.44.
*The real fell 0.3 percent to 1.6292 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
